      <p>This reference describes the XSLT 2.0 elements described in followed by several
         functions that are specific to XSLT (as distinct from XPath).</p>
      <p>The abstract elements <element>xsl:declaration</element> and
            <element>xsl:instruction</element> are not used in stylesheets. They
         define two substitution groups for top-level stylesheet declarations
         and processing instructions respectively.</p>

      <p>The details state the purpose of the element, with a note on usage, a
         list of attributes, and an example. Rather than repeat common
         attributes for each element, these attribute sets are listed after all
         the elements.</p>

